{
  "abstract": "It is appropriate that the technical sessions of the\r\nSorghum in the Eighties Symposium should start\r\nwith the physical environment because it is the\r\nmedium in which the biological material expresses\r\nitself. The \"properties\" of the medium such as\r\nradiation, rainfall, temperature, and soils control\r\nthe rate of the biological processes such as\r\nnutrient uptake, photosynthesis, respiration, dry\r\nmatter accumulation, etc. An understanding of the\r\ninteractions between the properties and processes\r\nshould lead us to develop principles for\r\nimproved productivity of the sorghum crop.",
